@startuml rag-pipeline
title RAG Pipeline — Ingestion & Query

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #444
    ActorBorderColor #444
    LifeLineBorderColor #888
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
    ParticipantBorderColor #6366F1
    BoxBackgroundColor #F0F4FF
    BoxBorderColor #C7D2FE
    NoteBackgroundColor #FEF9C3
    NoteBorderColor #EAB308
}

'--------------------------------------------------------------
' PART 1 — INGESTION (offline, run once or on doc change)
'--------------------------------------------------------------

box "Ingestion Flow (offline — run: python -m app.rag.ingest)" #F0FFF4
    participant "Markdown Docs\n(database-design.md)" as DOCS  #D1FAE5
    participant "Chunker"   as CHK  #A7F3D0
    participant "Embedder"  as EMB  #6EE7B7
    participant "ChromaDB\n(vector store)"  as VDB  #34D399
    participant "BM25 Index\n(in-memory)"   as BM25 #34D399
end box

== Ingestion ==

DOCS ->  CHK  : raw Markdown text
note right of CHK
  Strategy: split on ## / ### headers
  - Each section = one or more chunks
  - Max 500 tokens per chunk
  - 50-token overlap between adjacent chunks
  - Metadata attached per chunk:
      source_file, section_title, table_name
  Example chunk:
    section: "remittance.transaction"
    text: "Primary operational table.
           Columns: internal_transaction_id (PK),
           status, hub_id, service_id,
           remittance_amount ..."
end note
CHK  --> DOCS : chunks[ ] with metadata

CHK  ->  EMB  : chunk texts (batch ≤ 100)
note right of EMB
  If OPENAI_API_KEY set:
    model: text-embedding-3-small (cloud)
  Else (local fallback):
    model: nomic-embed-text via
    Ollama at localhost:11434/v1
end note
EMB  --> CHK  : embeddings[ ] (float vectors)

CHK  ->  VDB  : upsert chunks + embeddings\n(collection: ai_ops_portal_docs)
CHK  ->  BM25 : build BM25Okapi index\nover all chunk texts
BM25 --> CHK  : index cached in memory

note over VDB, BM25
  GET /api/v1/rag/status
  → { doc_count, last_ingested_at, collection_name }
end note

@enduml

@startuml rag-query
title RAG Pipeline — Query Flow

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #444
    ActorBorderColor #444
    LifeLineBorderColor #888
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
    ParticipantBorderColor #6366F1
    BoxBackgroundColor #F0F4FF
    BoxBorderColor #C7D2FE
    NoteBackgroundColor #FEF9C3
    NoteBorderColor #EAB308
}

actor       User         as U
participant "Frontend\nKnowledgeBase page" as FE  #EEF2FF
participant "FastAPI\nai-service"          as API #EEF2FF
participant "Retriever\n(hybrid search)"  as RTV #DBEAFE
participant "ChromaDB"   as VDB  #D1FAE5
participant "BM25 Index" as BM25 #D1FAE5
participant "claude-opus-4-6" as LLM #FCE7F3

'--------------------------------------------------------------
' PART 2 — QUERY (runtime, per user request)
'--------------------------------------------------------------

== Step 1: User asks a knowledge question ==

U   ->  FE  : "What columns carry PII\nin remittance.transaction?"
FE  ->  API : POST /api/v1/rag/query\n{ "question": "..." }

== Step 2: Embed the question ==

API ->  RTV : question text
RTV ->  RTV : embed question\n(same model used at ingestion time)

== Step 3: Dual retrieval — vector + BM25 ==

RTV ->  VDB  : cosine similarity search\n(top-8 semantic matches)
VDB --> RTV  : ranked chunks [ ] with scores

RTV ->  BM25 : keyword search — BM25Okapi\n(top-8 term frequency matches)
BM25 --> RTV : ranked chunks [ ]

== Step 4: Merge with Reciprocal Rank Fusion ==

RTV ->  RTV  : RRF merge
note right of RTV
  Reciprocal Rank Fusion (k=60):

  For each chunk in both lists:
    rrf_score += 1 / (rank + k)

  Final ranking = sum of rrf_scores
  across vector list + BM25 list.

  Return top-6 unique chunks.

  Why RRF?
  - Vector search is good for semantic
    similarity ("PII", "sensitive data")
  - BM25 is good for exact terms
    ("sender_msisdn", "recipient_fullname")
  - RRF combines both without tuning
    a fusion weight hyperparameter.
end note
RTV --> API  : top-6 chunks\n[ { chunk_text, section_title, source_file, score } ]

== Step 5: Grounding guard ==

alt max retrieval score < 0.4
    API --> FE : { answer: "Not enough relevant\ncontext found.", sources: [] }
    FE  --> U  : "Not enough relevant context found."
    note right of API
      Guard prevents hallucination:
      if the docs don't contain the answer,
      Claude is not asked — silence is safer
      than a confident wrong answer.
    end note
end

== Step 6: Claude answers grounded in context ==

API ->  LLM : system prompt + numbered context blocks\n+ user question
note right of LLM
  Prompt structure:
  ---
  You are a technical assistant. Answer
  ONLY using the context below. Cite the
  context block number for each claim.

  [1] section: remittance.transaction
  text: "PII columns: sender_msisdn,
  sender_fullname, sender_dob,
  sender_email, recipient_msisdn..."

  [2] section: Data Sources
  text: "PII columns — mask in logs
  and AI prompts..."

  Question: What columns carry PII?
  ---
end note

LLM --> API : answer text (with [1], [2] citations)

== Step 7: Return answer + source cards ==

API --> FE  : { answer: "The PII columns are...\n[1][2]",\n  sources: [ {chunk, section, score}, ... ] }
FE  --> U   : answer text\n+ collapsible source cards\n  (section_title + snippet per chunk)

@enduml
